======================================================================
CAN b1(T)=0 WITH ALL b1(T\v)=1?
======================================================================

If b1(T)=0, HYP-278 reduces to: NOT ALL of b1(T\v) are 1.
i.e., there exists v with b1(T\v) = 0.

Testing this exhaustively at n=5,6 and sampled at larger n.


